807
00:58:06.000 --> 00:58:08.125
Trafalgar is a zombie.
It's rhyming slang innit?

808
00:58:08.125 --> 00:58:09.417
How is it?

809
00:58:09.500 --> 00:58:14.000
Well. Trafalgar Square; fox and hare;
hairy Greek; five-day week;

810
00:58:14.000 --> 00:58:19.042
weak and feeble; pins and needles;
needle and stitch; Abercrombie and Fitch

811
00:58:19.167 --> 00:58:22.083
Abercrombie... Zombie!

812
00:58:22.792 --> 00:58:25.167
- Innit?
- Oh. Lord.

813
00:58:26.167 --> 00:58:27.542
All right. well. how about it?

814
00:58:27.542 --> 00:58:31.125
Why don't we go out there and face them?
Go down fighting? What do you think?

815
00:58:31.458 --> 00:58:35.125
But. somebody might come.
Somebody might rescue us.

816
00:58:35.208 --> 00:58:37.500
Nobody cares. We're on our own.

817
00:58:37.542 --> 00:58:41.167
We're old-age pensioners!
We gotta take care of ourselves!

818
00:58:54.125 --> 00:58:56.125
Looks like we already
sealed off the East End.

819
00:58:56.125 --> 00:58:56.958
We'll be fine.

820
00:59:00.125 --> 00:59:02.708
So. this is how it will end. eh?
The army?

821
00:59:04.917 --> 00:59:09.083
Yeah. 'course they will...
Yeah. maybe.

822
00:59:13.042 --> 00:59:13.875
Maybe.

823
00:59:32.583 --> 00:59:36.042
Wait! Be careful! Shit!

824
00:59:42.417 --> 00:59:45.250
Everyone's been evacuated
to the Hinzman RAF base.

825
00:59:45.250 --> 00:59:46.958
